article.headline: Bradley 85, Evansville 76
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Will Franklin had 21 points, four rebounds and four assists to lead Bradley to an 85-78 win over Evansville Saturday night. The Braves (10-4) tied Evansville (9-5) eight times, ending the first half at 35-35. Bradley broke a 71-71 tie with an eight-point streak in the final three minutes of the game. Franklin was 5-for-7 from the 3-point line while Bradley's Daniel Ruffin, who was 5-for-8 from the 3-point line, added 17 points. Zach Andrews and Jeremy Crouch each added 11. The Purple Aces, who shot 61.9 percent in the second half, were lead by Matt Webster, Bradley Strickland and Kyle Anslinger who each had 20 points. Webster had eight rebounds and Anslinger was 3-for-6 from the 3-point line. The Aces shot 55.1 percent for the game, but their bench scored only 10 points to Bradley's 26. Bradley shot 45.2 percent.
